Distribution ManagerAn employment opportunity is available in our Albany market as a Distribution Manager.
Essential Functions include: Possess a valid driver’s license and ability to obtain a valid CDL with additional endorsements preferred. Conduct the day to day dispatching of service installs, repairs and cleanings to customers throughout the designated market. Maintain the Service Technicians daily schedules and dispatch the technicians as service calls are completed. Schedule return trips with customers when necessary. Must productively multitask and efficiently navigate industry specific software. Utilize various in-truck technologies to help in the prevention of inefficiencies or safety concerns. Manage all noted deficiencies and ensuring immediate action is taken to resolve the deficiency. Perform weekly inspections/walk through of your designated fleet. Conduct the day to day dispatching of Drivers for deliveries throughout the designated market. Manage and maintain maintenance records and the timely service of designated equipment 100% of the time. Manage truck and vehicle maintenance record to ensure that all vehicles adhere to company policies and procedures. Maintain the delivery drivers schedule and forecast workload. Maintain customer database with current information.
Qualifications: Must be self-motivated, self-starter, results driven individual with a high degree of accuracy and attention to detail. Knowledge of heating and ventilation equipment preferred. Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite. 2-5 years industry specific experience preferred. Possess a high school/vocational school diploma or G.E.D. and related certification. CTEP qualifications-if not currently certified will need to obtain within 1 year of employment and maintain these certifications.
